    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1929-03-17T10:45:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1929-03-17T10:45:00-05:00" n="626"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d626">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">817.00/6236: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Minister in Nicaragua</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Eberhardt</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Managua</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1929-03-17T10:00:00-05:45"
                            >March 17, 1929—10 a.m.</date>
                        <lb/>[Received 9 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>72. Brigade headquarters reports that on March 14 marine patrol encountered a
                    group of bandits at Department of Chinandega, two miles west of San Juan de
                    Limay. One bandit killed. On March 15th combined marine and <hi rend="italic"
                        >voluntario</hi> force encountered bandits in the same vicinity, killing
                    four and capturing three. No marine or <hi rend="italic">voluntario</hi>
                    casualties. Marines believe that bandits constituted Salgado’s main group and
                    that they crossed into Honduras about March 16th.</p>
                <p>Repeated to Tegucigalpa.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Eberhardt</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
